      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Both did not work for me. I also thought it was an &quot;AND&quot; not an or? I see the Start-Class:  correctly in the MANIFEST.MF, but spring starts a different annotated @SpringBootApplication main class. I actually need that class for bootstrapping some things so I do not really like to change the annotation. Simply removing it did not work anyway. Spring seems to start the first main() it finds. I&#39;m using spring-boot-starter-parent 2.2.0.M3."
