    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you're using spring-boot-starter-parent in your pom, you simply add the following to your pom:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;build&gt;\n    &lt;plugins&gt;\n        &lt;plugin&gt;\n            &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;\n            &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;/plugin&gt;\n    &lt;/plugins&gt;\n&lt;/build&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Then do your mvn package.</p>\n\n<p>See <a href=\"http://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/1.2.5.RELEASE/reference/html/getting-started-first-application.html#getting-started-first-application-executable-jar\" rel=\"noreferrer\">this Spring docs page</a>.</p>\n\n<p>A very important aspect here is to mention that the directory structure has to be src/main/java/nameofyourpackage </p>\n"
  }, {
